  "name": "Ephesians 5:21–6:9",
  "localizedName": "Ephesians 5:21–6:9",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul taught how people in God’s family must treat their human family. In Paul’s time, families usually included a husband, a wife, children and slaves. Men had the most authority in the family. Women, children and slaves had to obey them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Yet serving Jesus as Lord changed the way people acted in their families. They had to follow Jesus’ example. Jesus is a "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108059",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "leader who serves"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and he "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108256",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "sacrificed"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " himself for the good of others. Every member of the family was to treat one another with love and respect. The one who had the most authority in the family was Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul called God the Master of all believers. He reminded them that God didn’t treat any one believer as more important than another. Men, women, children and slaves were all part of the church. The church is so important to Jesus that Paul described the relationship like a "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108206",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "marriage"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". The church being joined closely to Jesus is part of God’s plan. It shows God’s desire to save the whole world."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
